      date: "2023-08-01T19:31:00+00:00",
      review:
        "God, I adore this movie. It feels like a story to be passed on for generations. The animation is just fantastic. Such skill and love went into every frame. The writhing of demons was done in such a way that I felt squeamish just looking at them. Ashitaka is a powerful, but flat character. He doesn't change, though I felt he didn't need to. He was mature, brave, and strong in the face of such adversity. He is someone to aspire to be, despite his obvious naïveté. The Princess is lovely, a human among wolves who chooses to remain a wolf. I've never been muchof an environmentalist, but this film sure does make me want to start a garden. It felt odd having no set villains, or at least, the antagonists continuing to live. Lady Eboshi was such a good character, very conflicting were and are my feelings for her. On one hand, she wants to behead the forest spirit to save Irontown, but on the other hand, she cares for the needy and wants the best for the people in her town. The characters, animation, and score all coalesce into this beautiful work that I never had the desire to look away from, only to bask in its love and wonder.",
