      review:
        "Sword Art Online Abridged is probably the best anime of all time. Characters, humour, plot, inside jokes, animation, voice acting, ALL 10/10 Available to watch on youtube for free. You have no excuse not to watch it. Not only that but the show has only improved over the years. Episode 17 is one of the best anime episodes ever and it came from a parody? How is this possible? I don't know. Nothing makes sense any more. The fact they spend 6 months on each episode probably helps. Each episode is gold. No filler,no boring parts, no plot holes or stupid 2D characters,  just laughing crying and adventure.\n\nSword Art Online the original is ok.  Really liked the first 14 episodes. It made me care enough about the characters enough to overlook plot and writing issues, and also drag myself through the rest of the series.  \n\nIf you hated SAO You will love SAO  Abridged\nIf you loved SAO You will love SAO  Abridged\nIf you never watched SAO You will love SAO  Abridged (and don't bother watching SAO, Abridged is all you need)\n\nSo to recap I gave SAO 8/10 for making the first 14 episodes and the source animation for  SAO  Abridged",
