      date: "2023-08-01T17:57:00+00:00",
      review:
        "KnY S3 is good. It is not on par with S2. If S2 is 8.8/10, then S3 is the 8.3/10 that it has on here. It doesn't meet the marks that S2 does, but still, S3 was enjoyable. It's content that you turn off your brain and binge with ease. This series garners a lot of criticism, and I'm one who didn't really like S1. The animation throughout the series is great, but the one problem has always been its lacking storyline. It's very shallow, and we lack information, in exchange for fights and animation. This isfine, I don't think the storyline is anywhere near the trash that comes out of Hollywood, so KnY will pretty much always be a series I can rely on to deliver. \n\nAnimation 10/10\n-  It's Ufotable.\nSound 10/10\n-  Great OP ED, good BGM and impactful soundtrack at the end.\nStory 5/10\n-  It's about getting his sword, and includes fights, other than that, the story just lacks expansion of our knowledge of this world.\nCharacters 9/10\n-  Mitsuri was a nice character to delve into, I really wanted to know more of her story, and see more of her on the battlefield.  Genya and Muichirou were ok.  I was kind of glad we didn't have to hear much obnoxious crying from Zenitsu.\nEnjoyment 8/10\n-  Like I said, it was good, not great, but was easy to binge.  Simple brain food for someone looking to just enjoy the simple stuff this series offers.\n\nI recommend KnY to everyone, especially those who have no enemies.",
