      date: "2023-08-01T10:52:00+00:00",
      review:
        "Violet evergarden was majestic. everything in it, the art, the animation, the writing and the emotions were beautiful. while watching it i have felt emotions that i haven't felt in a long time. The anime starts with violet, emotionless, robotic, calling herself a weapon for major Gilbert. as the war ended, she had no purpose. because of that she demanded to be \"thrown away\". after hearing that prisedent Hodgins decided to take her to his company so she can work. she wasn't suitable at anything she did. but then she learns about the auto memory doll service. auto memory dolls are girls who write letters for peoplewho can't write, crafting the customer's emotions into a proper beautiful letter. Violet is watching the doll at work when she hears the phrase \"I love you\", a phrase that she heard before from major Gilbert but does not know the meaning of, so she starts to work as an auto memory doll in pursuit of learning the meaning of \"I love you\".\n\nthe emotions in Violet Evergarden are portrayed beautifully. as viewers we go with Violet through everything in her journy to learn emotions, because of that every smile, tear, frown is so much more heavier to me, when Violet cries, her tears are much more impactful because we know she couldn't cry before, we see how with every customer and letter she writes, she makes progress, she 'feel' things for the first time, all the people Violet meet through her job have beautiful stories of their own as we see how Violet go through them, all the characters are interesting with many complex emotions that Violet tries to figure out. these individual stories are my favorite part of the anime, many of them made me tear up. these stories are so perfect.\n\nwhen Violet learns how to empathize, she starts to regret, she is burning from her past, her regret is heartbreaking and feels too real, i don't wanna spoil it, i hated seeing her like that.\n\nThe art in Violet Evergarden is a master piece, the art completes every emotional/gorgeous scene, every scene in Violate Evergarden feels like a breath of fresh air, the colors are cozy and every character is so pretty. Violet clothes are very pretty too and well designed, and also the calming ambient... man everything is beautiful. if i wanted to describe the whole anime in a word it would be \"beautiful\"\n\nthe fact that Violet Evergarden made me feel the most amount of emotions out of all things i have watched in my life is enough for me. this show is a master piece.\n\nfavorite episode: ep10\n\n5/5",
