      review:
        "Trigun Stampede accomplishes extremely well what Netflix’s Cannon Busters tried (and failed) to do. Both are violent, gritty, and set in a post-apocalyptic, wild-west-meets-cyberpunk world, but Trigun succeeds by keeping the focus on the mystery of its title character: Vash the Stampede. The (fully CGI) animation is stunning, and there is something so captivating about this dismal, decaying world. It’s a slow burn story but with plenty of action, heart, and imagination, all culminating in a visually astonishing finale. If you come into this wearing nostalgia glasses you're going to be disappointed as it watches nothing like its predecessor. Instead, treat it like you're tryinggiant sand worm meat for the first time... you may just be delighted.",
