      date: "2023-07-31T13:56:00+00:00",
      review:
        "I'll judge the first 2 seasons on this review). What can I say about 86? It's a must-see! Let's talk about the obvious. 86 is sublime in its animation. Whether it's the fight scenes, the landscapes, the quieter moments, the details, the characters, the cities, the robots, ... Everything is well done, there are no mistakes, everything is successful. The work is sublime. The scene that most illustrates this beauty is clearly the one in the rose field. Now that we've talked image, let's talk story. It's very well told. Right from the start, we see the social class system present in society between the \"grayhairs\" and the others. We understand Milizé's ambitions in relation to the latter. The author makes this very interesting, as Milizé's desire to create friendship is not directly accepted by his troops. They're not dumb characters who don't distrust nice people. What's more, despite the relationship that gradually develops. Certain tragic events remind the heroes of the story that this friendship is only very fragile. \nIt will obviously grow stronger with each battle and discussion. The Handler gradually manages to shake the Reaper out of his natural coldness and seriousness. If you want to talk a little about season 2, take a look at the adventure surrounding Frederica Rosenfort. Some may find her useless and unbearable at first, but the ending will make you forget all that very quickly.",
