      review:
        "\"Bleach\" was unlucky to come out when there are many alternative Shounen that are all like two identical drops of water. There are a lot of interesting characters in Bleach, funny dramatic ones, the characters die there, it's still frankly a teenage title, but he has iron balls in terms of acting dramaturgy... but this is mainstream, now all shounen will look like this. I read manga as a teenager and I'm glad the anime came out, but I'm honest with you there's nothing special about it. the art style is good, but not more, the animation is acceptable, but I know what can be better the music isgood, but I wouldn't listen to it separately on repeat\n\nthis title has one big plus there are few fillers and a lot of action\n\nwell, there's probably an interesting lore of the entire franchise, but I spread my hands and can't advise, it's exclusively for fans\n\nwell, this is a very straightforward quotation of manga, personally I think that a good anime adaptation of manga should be a good ANIME... in manga, there is a special genre where the characters pronounce their actions so that the reader can understand what is happening, in a good anime adaptation this should not be, anime works a little differently, there are pictures moving and you need to show and not tell. the adaptation should complement the manga and not quote it\n\nin fact, I'm lying, the fact is that in manga fights are vague garbage and anime looks more interesting, this is not an achievement of adaptation, but rather a bad manga... yes, I understand that I'm climbing into a bottle, but this is such a genre here just a good Shounen is not enough",
