      date: "2023-07-31T12:38:00+00:00",
      review:
        "The CGI Resident Evil films in my opinion were always WAY more miss than hit and the only people that liked them or at least were willing to look past their massive issues due to their love for the characters were huge fans of the Resident Evil IP . Up until now I can't say that I've liked any of these original stories all that much beyond the novelty of \"Oh look there's Rebecca , Sure haven't seen her in a while!\" but Death Island was a surprisingly enjoyable pop corn flick Now don't get me wrong the bar wasn't set very high with Vendettaand especially Infinite Darkness but I found the action to be well choreographed and the animation to be pretty good overall . They tried to do some interesting things here with Jill's PTSD of sorts after the events of Resident Evil 5 and the main villain actually calling out how hypocritical and ineffectual the main cast of this series has been but nothing gets enough time in the oven and overall both plot points disappoint \n\nNobody will or should see this film expecting masterful writing or complex character motivations . This is nothing but a fanservice movie where damn near all the fan favorites come together (I do miss old Jill though but new one is fine) to defeat yet another bio-terror threat and that's all there is to it\n\nRecommend it to Resident Evil fans and nobody else",
