      date: "2023-07-29T06:34:00+00:00",
      review:
        "A revenge fantasy with glimmers of an intriguing narrative, but lack of focus undercuts its potential. Story: 4/10 The betrayed player sent back in time premise shows promise and offers some interesting lore reveals. However, abrupt time skips and pacing issues cause the narrative to feel disjointed at times. The ending cuts off abruptly with no resolution. Art: 7/10 The polished, clean art style serves the story adequately. Action flows smoothly when present. Character designs are somewhat generic but serviceable. Characters: 3/10 The protagonist is an average power fantasy vessel, but his ruthless pursuit of revenge has its appeal. Supporting characters are one-note. Antagonists' motivations remain unclear.Enjoyment: 5/10\nDespite issues with narrative flow and weak characterization, I still found the revenge-driven plot moderately entertaining. The story showed sparks of potential.\n\nIn summary, Kill the Hero is a deeply flawed but sporadically entertaining revenge fantasy. Buried under messy plotting are glimmers of an intriguing narrative. It may appeal to power fantasy fans willing to overlook its issues.",
